The issue is that RabbitMQ doesn't auto-propagate W3C Trace Context like HTTP does. You must manually **inject** context into message headers on publish and **extract** it on consume.

## Publisher (Service A)

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;
using OpenTelemetry;
using OpenTelemetry.Context.Propagation;

// Create a shared ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA");
static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("order.publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into message headers
Propagator.Inject(
    new PropagationContext(activity!.Context, Baggage.Current),
    props.Headers,
    (headers, key, value) => headers[key] = value);

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

## Consumer (Service B)

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB");
static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

// When consuming:
var parentContext = Propagator.Extract(
    default,
    ea.BasicProperties.Headers,
    (headers, key) =>
    {
        if (headers != null && headers.TryGetValue(key, out var val))
            return [System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])val)];
        return [];
    });

Baggage.Current = parentContext.Baggage;

using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
    "order.process",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentContext.ActivityContext);  // <-- links to parent trace

// ... handle message
```

## Required setup (both services)

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA") // or "ServiceB"
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

## Why it works

- `Propagator.Inject` writes `traceparent` and `tracestate` into RabbitMQ headers
- `Propagator.Extract` reads them back and reconstructs the parent context
- Starting the consumer activity with `parentContext.ActivityContext` links both spans under **one distributed trace**

> **Tip:** If you switch to [MassTransit](https://masstransit.io/) or [Wolverine](https://wolverine.netlify.app/), this propagation is handled automatically. The manual approach above is needed when using the raw `RabbitMQ.Client` library.
